      "date": "2014-06-06 21:14:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nFirst, thanks again for this patch!  It is going to work just fine for us as a workaround.\n\nIf we decide to land this, we really also need to filter system.posix_acl_access from the listxattr listing when posix_acl_access is just an empty acl list.\n\nAgain, this fixes our crashing-clients problem, but it means that posix_acl_access appears in the listing but returns an error code when we try to access it.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "2234d4806300536b4ad76622d2ad9bd7afa99198",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-06-07 00:12:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThen, would you mind the patch to remove the empty ACL when getxattr find it, then the next listxattr/getxattr will not find it again? Such case will be similar as the case of race: remove the xattr between listxattr and getxattr.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
